    "result": {"data":{"markdownRemark":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Potercha","names":[{"name":"потерча́","plural":"потерча́та","language":"Ukrainian"},{"name":"збігленя́","plural":"збігленя́та","language":"Ukrainian"},{"name":"потерчу́к","plural":"потерчуки́","language":"Ukrainian"}],"description":"A small demon or undead, formed from the soul of a deceased child","related":[],"origin":[{"value":"Ukraine","comment":null,"sometimes":false}],"taxonomy":[{"value":"demon","comment":null,"sometimes":false},{"value":"spirit","comment":null,"sometimes":false},{"value":"undead","comment":null,"sometimes":false}],"shapeshifting":[{"value":"no data","comment":null,"sometimes":false}],"activityTime":[{"value":"no data","comment":null,"sometimes":false}],"voice":[{"value":"croaking","comment":"sounds like a frog-like croaking","sometimes":false}],"character":[{"value":"no data","comment":null,"sometimes":false}],"appearance":[{"value":"childlike","comment":null,"sometimes":false}],"clothes":[{"value":"no data","comment":null,"sometimes":false}],"paraphernalia":[{"value":"nightlight","comment":"a small lamp used to lure people into a trap, the origin of will-o'-the-wisp or ignis fatuus","sometimes":false}],"number":[{"value":"common","comment":null,"sometimes":false}],"habitat":[{"value":"lake","comment":null,"sometimes":false},{"value":"wetland","comment":"swamp, marsh, bog, fen","sometimes":false}],"wikipedia":null,"image":"..\\static\\assets\\images\\night-g7d4fb2ad6_1920.jpg"},"html":"<h2 id=\"Description\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#Description\" aria-label=\"Description permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\"><path fill=\"currentColor\" fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Description</h2>\n<p>Potercha is formed from a stillborn, aborted child or a child deceased unbaptized. It exists during 7 years. If no one performs a ritual (see Rituals below) over the potercha, then it would be transformed into a different demon forever.</p>\n<h2 id=\"Etymology\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#Etymology\" aria-label=\"Etymology permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\"><path fill=\"currentColor\" fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Etymology</h2>\n<p>From Ukrainian «потеряти» (poteriaty) or «потирати» (potyraty) - to loose, spoil, harm, destroy. There is also a phrase «потеряти дитя» (poteraty dytia - to loose a child) - to have a miscarriage.</p>\n<h2 id=\"Analogues-in-other-cultures\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#Analogues-in-other-cultures\" aria-label=\"Analogues in other cultures permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\"><path fill=\"currentColor\" fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Analogues in other cultures</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Poroniec (Poland)</li>\n<li>Myling (Sweden)</li>\n<li>Utburd (Norway)</li>\n<li>Drekavac, Дрекавац (Southern Slavs: Serbia, Croatia, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Montenegro)</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"External-Links\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#External-Links\" aria-label=\"External Links permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\"><path fill=\"currentColor\" fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>External Links</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Image by <a href=\"https://pixabay.com/users/yuri_b-2216431/?utm_source=link-attribution&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=image&amp;utm_content=3078326\">Yuri_B</a> from <a href=\"https://pixabay.com/?utm_source=link-attribution&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=image&amp;utm_content=3078326\">Pixabay</a></li>\n</ul>"}},"pageContext":{"language":{"name":"English","code":"en","path":"","dateFormat":"DD/MM/YYYY"},"locale":"en","id":"4ef8e1739cf344109bdbf04efbce101a","localizedLinks":{"en":{"path":"/creatures/potercha"},"uk":{"path":"/істоти/потерча"},"ru":{"path":"/существа/потерча"}}}},
